{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-26T03:09:53.144Z","tool_name":"replace","tool_id":"replace_1777172993143_0","parameters":{"instruction":"Update architecture doc to reflect that per-mode FX presets are now handled by EffectsBus instead of SamplerDispatcher.","file_path":"docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md","old_string":"| `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py` | `SamplerDispatcher` — turns a `(SampleRecord, params)` pair into the OSC bundle that triggers the granular voice. Acquires a buffer through the loader, applies the per-mode FX preset, ships `/s_new sw_sampler bufnum=… grain_size=… density=…`, and returns a handle for sustained voices to release later. Folds the per-sample `gain_db` into the synth `amp` so peak-normalized captures play back at consistent loudness. |\n","new_string":"| `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py` | `SamplerDispatcher` — turns a `(SampleRecord, params)` pair into the OSC bundle that triggers the granular voice. Acquires a buffer through the loader, ships `/s_new sw_sampler bufnum=… grain_size=… density=…`, and returns a handle for sustained voices to release later. Folds the per-sample `gain_db` into the synth `amp` so peak-normalized captures play back at consistent loudness. `EffectsBus` (also in this file) manages the per-mode FX preset application to the shared bus. |\n","allow_multiple":false}}
{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-04-26T03:09:53.170Z","tool_id":"replace_1777172993143_0","status":"success"}
